  "text": "The experimental setup is described in Sect. 2 and includes five flow configurations. Each type of roughness (bed roughness and cylinder array) is investigated under uniform flow conditions. Special attention is given to the flow in the near-bed region within the cylinder array and to the free surface oscillation phenomenon (seiching). The results of this part of the study are presented in Sect. 3. The uniform flows are used as references for studying the roughness transitions, which are presented in Sect. [CITATION_1] . The water depth response to the roughness transition is first investigated and a 1D momentum equation is used to predict the water surface profile. The response of velocity and turbulence is then analysed. Finally, Sect. 4 ends with the effect of flow non-uniformity on free surface oscillations.",
